The dynamics of LDH, LT and PLR during early treatment may also play an important role in patient response to immunotherapy in line with our results. According to the JM model output, intercept and slope estimated in the longitudinal submodel we could identify the expected trajectory of these features. Deviations from this linear trajectory are associated with changes in the predicted progression risk, modifying the HR originally estimated in the survival submodel (Fig. 2A) according to the dynamics of the monitored feature. MV-JM results suggest that a fast increasing LDH value, a fast decreasing LT value, and a slow decreasing PLR value from the predicted baseline values (LDH = 329.94 U/L, LT = 1543.98 /\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
